    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `vim.pack.add()`, setting the `version` field to the name of the default branch is not equivalent to setting the `version` field to `nil` if the default branch is changed by the remote.\n\n---\n\nI discovered this bug when trying to update my nvim-treesitter config from the old `master` branch to the new `main` branch. My config looked like this:\n\n```lua\nvim.pack.add {\n  {\n    src = 'https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n    version = 'master',\n  },\n}\n```\n\nI deleted the `version = 'master',` line, which because `main` is now the default branch, should result in the version defaulting to `main`. I then ran `:lua vim.pack.update()`, but saw no changes:\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0cad2091-45be-481c-90f7-0e9ca1962ec6\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nThis issue only occurs when the locally cloned repository still has the old branch set as the default. The changed default is not checked.\n\n- Create this `init.lua`:\n  ```lua\n  vim.pack.add {\n    {\n      src = 'https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n      version = 'master',\n    },\n  }\n  \n  -- Simulate the default branch still being 'master' at the time it was cloned.\n  -- This was the case back when I added nvim-treesitter, but it has since been changed to 'main'.\n  vim.system(\n    { 'git', 'remote', 'set-head', 'origin', 'master' },\n    { cwd = vim.fn.stdpath('data') .. '/site/pack/core/opt/nvim-treesitter' }\n  )\n  ```\n- After launching vim, replace `init.lua` with this:\n  ```lua\n  vim.pack.add {\n    {\n      src = 'https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n    },\n  }\n  ```\n- Run `:lua vim.pack.update()`. You will get no updates.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`vim.pack` updates the plugin to the origin's default branch.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+2084-e2bc84e31\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.43.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nFedora COPR",
