            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for the issue!\n\n> When using `vim.pack.add()`, setting the `version` field to the name of the default branch is not equivalent to setting the `version` field to `nil` if the default branch is changed by the remote.\n\nThis is not *quite* the problem: `version=nil` always points to the default branch. The problem seems to be that `vim.pack.update()` doesn't react to change in default branch on the origin.\n\nIt is the same behavior with simple `git fetch --force origin` outside of `vim.pack.update()`.\n\nI'll have to investigate if this is at all possible (probably should be). But even if not, reacting to changing of the origin's default branch doesn't seem like a use case to go extra mile to account for. Deleting and reinstalling plugin is more or less an acceptable solution here.",
